# API Observability Baseline

Use this when implementing or modifying API runtime behavior, request handling, and operational diagnostics.

## Request tracing
- Must include a request identifier for every request (`requestId` or equivalent).
- Must propagate correlation identifiers across internal calls when present.
- Must include request ID in structured error responses/log events where applicable.

## Structured logging
- Must emit structured logs (key-value fields), not ad-hoc free text only.
- Must include at least: `requestId`, route/module name, status/result, and duration for key operations.
- Must not log secrets, tokens, passwords, or sensitive PII.

## Metrics and health
- Must expose baseline service health and readiness checks.
- Readiness must validate critical dependencies (for example database/cache) and not only process liveness.
- Should expose baseline latency/error-rate counters or equivalent metrics hooks.

## Error observability
- Must map domain errors consistently and preserve a machine-readable code when available.
- Must capture enough context to triage production incidents without exposing internal implementation details to clients.

